  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 04:43 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Signal is HURTING Performance + PM Bot Restart Loop\n\n**Task:** Run copy-intel-tracker, analyze copy signal correlation with trade outcomes. Fix PM bot stability.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Copy signal is degrading WR, not improving it:**\n\n| Copy Signal | WR | Trades |\n|---|---|---|\n| No copy signal | **76.9%** | 13 |\n| bearish@100 | 50.0% | 10 |\n| bearish_low | 50.0% | 8 |\n| bullish@100 | **25.0%** | 4 |\n| bullish_low | 50.0% | 2 |\n\nTrades WITHOUT copy signal: 77% WR. Trades WITH copy: ~45% WR. The copy conviction boost (+1 to aligned count) is letting marginal trades through that lose at coinflip rate.\n\n2. **Current PM order flow: 100% bearish** (UP token: 0 bids/99 asks, DN token: 99 bids/0 asks) while BTC is flat at $67,430 in an uptrend. Classic divergence \u2014 PM flow is lagging the rally.\n\n3. **HL leaderboard: BTC 9L/2S** \u2014 overwhelming long bias from top traders. ETH 5L/6S (mixed), SOL 6L/4S (slight long).\n\n4. **PM bot infrastructure fix:** Killed rogue test process (pid 3832809) consuming resources. Bot was crashing because test process occupied the venv/connections. Restarted with **self-healing bash wrapper** (`while true; do ... sleep 10; done`) so screen won't die permanently.\n\n**My thinking:** The copy signal was rebuilt Mar 29 with 3 bug fixes, so all pre-Mar-29 copy data is tainted. The 37-trade sample includes mostly pre-fix data. But the pattern is clear: when copy agrees and boosts conviction, the added trades underperform. Two possible explanations:\n- (a) Copy signal was garbage pre-fix \u2192 poisoned data \u2192 ignore until we have post-fix sample\n- (b) Copy signal genuinely adds noise \u2192 the 4 core indicators ARE the edge, copy is false confidence\n\n**Decision:** \n- **Disable copy conviction boost for now.** Change `copy_conviction_boost = 0` (log copy signal but don't let it affect trade decisions). Wait for 30+ post-fix trades to re-evaluate.\n- NOT deploying at 4 AM \u2014 queue for Monday active hours.\n- Monitor: if no-copy WR holds at 70%+ over next 30 trades, keep boost disabled permanently.\n\n**Next P1 heartbeat:** After 30 trades with copy-boost disabled, compare WR vs the 37-trade baseline. Also analyze: do no-copy trades correlate with specific hours or bias levels?\n\n## 2026-03-30 04:28 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Regime Classifier Built + Fear & Greed Alpha Signal\n\n**Task:** Build BTC regime classifier for alpha research pipeline. Analyze Fear & Greed correlation. Wire new data source into confidence scoring.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Built `regime_classifier.py`** \u2014 standalone module that classifies BTC into 4 regimes using 5-min candle data:\n   - `RANGE` \ud83c\udfaf \u2014 PM contrarian trades work best (low vol, mean-reverting)\n   - `TREND` \ud83d\udcc8 \u2014 directional, orderly moves (PM risky, filter/reduce)\n   - `HIGH_VOL` \u26a1 \u2014 extreme moves (DO NOT trade PM)\n   - `CRASH_RECOVERY` \ud83d\udd04 \u2014 post-crash V-bounce (HL long bias signal)\n   - Uses: avg range, max range, volume ratio, net change, directional consistency\n   - Current output: TREND (UP), sc",
